The second season of Yakusoku no Neverland. Fifteen children escape Grace Field House, a false paradise, hoping for a chance at freedom. Instead, they encounter plants and animals they have never before seen, and are chased by demons. The outside world is so beautiful, and yet is almost too cruel to face. Even so, the children refuse to give up. They are guided in their search for better lives only by a message from Minerva and a pen Norman left behind in order to fulfill their promise to return to the House to save those of their family who are still trapped within.
(Source: Aniplex of America) Note: Episode 1 streamed early on Amazon Prime on Jan 7, 2021. The regular TV broadcast started on Jan 8, 2021.

[Question] A new different world hero appeared on Horizon [Answer] Turn back to Earth right now!
After the struggle, I saved the other world and tried to enjoy the rest of my life freely. But for some reason, the incarnating hero from the earth will spring up here on the Horizon. Don't be silly! This world is mine!
The Holy Knight, the Demon Girl, the Elves, the Beastmen, and even the ordinary people, everything in this world will never be given to anyone!
NEET? Izakaya? SDF? No matter who the enemy is! Other-hero, turn back to the Earth!
Drive back all the other world hero with wisdom, courage and perfection, a slapstick fantasy opens!
(Source: Kadokawa, translated)
Makenshi no Maken Niyoru Maken no Tame no Harem Life

An ever-righteous and sword-loving high schooler, Fujinomiya Soujirou is fatally stabbed by a robber during a home invasion. However, on the crossroads between life and death, "God" asks him if he wants to live a little longer. Clutching one of his prized swords, Soujirou agrees to a (cheatless) new life. Sent to another world, his only possessions are a talking sword "Hotarumaru" and the sword that took his life, "Sakura". He is also given the job title of "Cursed Sword Master", granting him the ability to bring out the "personality" of a sword. With a new realm of possibilities laid out before him, he sets forth on a journey to raise a harem of katanas, while begrudgingly hunting monsters and helping those in need.
